main event: On April 8, 1955, two whitish lights or glowing objects were observed in Gander, Newfoundland, hovering and growing in size.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 10 to 20 seconds,The observed lights appeared magnetic and erratic in movement,The source of the report was an RCAF military lieutenant,There was insufficient data for a definitive evaluation,The report concluded that the object was unidentified and could possibly be a balloon or aircraft.
sighted object: two whitish lights in the sky
